cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.DS 

This paper deals with optimization problems in learning overcomplete representations, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional dictionaries, which falls under the scope of cs.CV. The paper also involves the study of geometric properties of optimization landscapes, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the use of local search algorithms, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
